project: In pre-industrial society, high birth and death rates lead to slow population growth.
People depend on hunting and gathering, so food supplies are unpredictable.
The main concern is finding enough food to survive…
In the industrial society, life expectancy has increased.
The death rate drops due to better sanitation and food storage technology.
Although the birth rate is still high, the population increases rapidly.
The main concern is making enough money to avoid starvation due to poverty...
Use the Left & Right Arrow Keys to move
Use the Up Arrow Key to jump
Don't fall into the spikes or you'll have to start over!
Use the Up and Down Arrow Keys to climb the ladder
Collect the can and return to the entrance
